This is the README for JSON::Repair version 0.07.

JSON::Repair is a "module" for the Perl computer programming language, a
library of computer code to install on a computer.  This document contains
four sections:

1. About - what the module does

2. Documentation - how to learn more about the module

3. Installation - how to install this module on a computer

4. Help - what to do if you get stuck

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------

1. ABOUT

JSON::Repair - reformat JSON to strict compliance

Given some "relaxed" JSON text containing such things as trailing
commas, comments, or strings containing tab characters or newlines,
this module uses heuristics to convert these into strictly compliant
JSON.

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------

2. DOCUMENTATION

You can read the documentation for the module online at the following
websites:

    * http://search.cpan.org/perldoc?JSON::Repair
    * http://metacpan.org/release/JSON-Repair

(These links go to the latest version of the module.)

After installing the module, you can read the documentation on your
computer using

    perldoc JSON::Repair

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------

3. INSTALLATION

This module requires Perl version 5.14.1 or later.

To install the module from CPAN, use

    cpan JSON::Repair

If you have the App::cpanminus installer, you may prefer

    cpanm JSON::Repair

To install the module from the source file, JSON-Repair-0.07.tar.gz, follow
this sequence of commands:

    tar xfz JSON-Repair-0.07.tar.gz
    cd JSON-Repair-0.07
    perl Makefile.PL
    make
    make install

If you want to test the module before installing it, use "make test" after
"make" and before "make install".

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------

4. HELP

To get help with the module, you can email the author, Ben Bullock, at
<bkb@cpan.org>. If you think there is a problem in the module, you can
report a bug at 

<https://github.com/benkasminbullock/json-repair/issues>,

or if you want to alter the source code of JSON::Repair, try the public
repository on github at 

<https://github.com/benkasminbullock/json-repair>. 

